FBIS4-41923 "drsov125_g_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-125 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Assembly Urges Referendum on Confederation With Russia Assembly Urges Referendum on Confederation With Russia WS2806115094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 WS2806115094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network Belarusian BFN [Text] BELINFORM has been told by [name indistinct], head of the press service of the Belaya Rus-Slav Assembly Party, that early in July the Russian State Duma plans to discuss the possibility of creating a confederation between Belarus and Russia. Representatives of this party were invited to attend the discussion. The Belaya Rus-Slav Assembly press service also reported that the Party Duma addresses the Belarusian Supreme Soviet with a proposal to hold -- during the second round of presidential elections -- a referendum with regard to rendering official status to the Russian language in Belarus, the creation of a confederation with Russia, and the introduction of dual, Belarusian-Russian, citizenship.
